article.headline: Army 54, N.J. Tech 44
article.story: NEWARK, N.J. (AP) -- Jarell Brown scored 23 points to lead Army to a 54-44 win over the New Jersey Institute of Technology on Thursday night. Josh Miller added nine points and eight rebounds for the Black Knights (4-4), which never trailed. Jheryl Wilson had 16 points to lead the Highlanders (0-10), while Nesho Milosevic pulled down a game-high 13 rebounds. Army took command early on, jumping out to a 14-0 lead and led 29-19 at the break. The teams then traded baskets for most of the second half, but the Highlanders -- who committed 23 turnovers -- could not overcome their own sloppy play. Army also won the battle of the boards, outrebounding the Highlanders 35-33.
